  <summary>2/27/2001--Introduced.
Airline Merger Moratorium Act of 2001 - Makes it unlawful, for a one-year period, for a major air carrier to acquire assets or voting securities of another major airline carrier if with respect to such acquisition notice is required to be filed (based on certain qualifying criteria) to enable the Federal Trade Commission and the Assistant Attorney General, Antitrust Division, to determine whether the acquisition may violate U.S. antitrust laws.</summary>
